    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING PUMP: VICKERS (LUK) V10NF AND V20NF - OPERATION - PRESSURE PLATE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>PRESSURE PLATE</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0500505">Figure 5</hotlnk>
            for all Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0500505" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0500505" filename="../figg05/G0500505.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. Pressure Plate</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DISCHARGE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. VANE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. ROTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>6. SPRING</callout1>
                <callout1>7. PRESSURE IN CARTRIDGE</callout1>
                <callout1>8. PRESSURE PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>9. COVER-STD.</callout1>
                <callout1>10. BACK PRESSURE IN SYSTEM EFFECTIVE HERE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>The pressure plate (Item 8) seals the pumping chamber.</para>
        <para>A light spring (Item 6) holds the plate against the cartridge until pressure builds up in the system.
        </para>
        <para>System pressure pushes against the area at the back of the plate (Item 10), which is larger than the area
            exposed to the pumping cartridge.
        </para>
        <para>Thus, an unbalanced force holds the plate against the cartridge, sealing the cartridge and providing the
            proper running clearance for the rotor and vanes.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
